        <h1>Sámi languages</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"><img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_sprak150x113.jpg" alt="SamepolitikkFoto: Kenneth Hætta" /></div>
        
            <p class="textIngress">The Sámi language shall be a living language. Active and wider use of the Sámi language is an important element in the further development of Sámi culture.
</p>
        
            <img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_sprak150x113.jpg" alt="SamepolitikkFoto: Kenneth Hætta" class="temaIngressImg" />
        <div class="descriptionText"><p>Pursuant to § 1-5 of the Sami Act the Sami and the Norwegian languages are of equal worth. According to chapter 3 of the Sámi Act, Sámi and Norwegian are languages of equal status.within the administrative district for the Sámi languages, It is important that the Sámi language is used in the public context and that official information is also made available in Sámi to the Sámi population. The pages in Sámi on the Government’s website are the main channel for information from the Government and the Ministries in the Sámi language.<br /></p></div>
        <div style="clear:both"></div>
        
     </div>
         
    
                            
